    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-01-08T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-01-08T15:00:00-05:00" n="810"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d810">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.51/1177: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-01-08T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 8, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. From the Under Secretary. Pedregal<note n="20" xml:id="d810fn1">Guillerino del
                        Pedregál, Executive Vice President, Corporación de Fomento de la
                        Producción.</note> left for Santiago by airplane January 6. He came to see
                    me before leaving and expressed the hope that he might be able to return to
                    Washington within 3 weeks. His trip to Santiago is due to the resignation of
                        Wachholtz<note n="21" xml:id="d810fn2">Roberto Wachholtz, former Minister of
                        Finance.</note> and for the purpose of assuring himself that the new
                    Minister of Finance will continue to support him in his mission to this country.
                    Pedregal has made an admirable impression here, and the projects which he has
                    outlined to me seem to me constructive and practical.</p>
                <pb facs="0694" n="682" xml:id="pg_682"/>
                <p>The negotiations undertaken by Ambassador Bianchi<note n="22" xml:id="d810fn3"
                        >Manuel Bianchi, Chilean Ambassador to Spain on special mission in the
                        United States to purchase military supplies.</note> are continuing, and I
                    think he is fully aware of the fact that this Government is going out of its way
                    to try and find the opportunity for cooperation. I believe that a definite
                    decision with regard to this latter question may be expected in the near future.
                    [Welles.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
